---

{% submission %}

{% submission-part type="problem" %}

State testing is high stress and any error could potentially be a write up or your job. Teachers read from a book and then begin testing. We are supposed to work for 40 minutes then take a 3 minute stretch break, continue working for 40 minutes, then another break and so on until the allowed time has been met. We can’t have technology in the room for a timer. 

{% /submission-part %}

{% submission-part type="proposed-solution" %}

If you reference a “pregnancy wheel” that uses the first day of the last period to predict the due date…we need a wheel that whatever your start time + 40 minutes blacked out for working = *THIS IS WHEN YOU BREAK!!!*  **three minutes blacked out for the stretch break.** Whatever time is showing after the 3 minute break THIS is where you spin the wheel to start the 40 minutes again. A simple wheel that is laminated and could be used in the rooms would take an “error” possibility out! 

{% /submission-part %}

{% /submission %}